text: Great value! The $8 cheeseburger was juicy and cooked just right. Fries were perfectly crispy. Exactly what I want from a diner.
Solid diner breakfast. The $6 pancakes were fluffy and the coffee kept coming. Nothing fancy but reliable.
The $5 grilled cheese was soggy and the tomato soup tasted canned. Disappointing even for diner standards.
Best $5 milkshake in town! The $7 BLT was loaded with crispy bacon. Friendly service too.
The $4 hot dog was standard fare but the $4 onion rings were surprisingly good. Typical diner experience.
$4 chicken noodle soup was exactly what I needed - hearty and flavorful. Perfect comfort food on a cold day.
Classic diner breakfast done right. $6 pancakes with crispy bacon hit the spot. Coffee refills never stopped coming.
$8 cheeseburger was dry and overcooked. Fries were stale. Not worth it when there are better options nearby.
The $5 apple pie Ã  la mode was heavenly - flaky crust and perfect filling. Service was friendly and fast.
Good diner food at fair prices. The $7 BLT could use more bacon, but the $3 fries were excellent.
